Cell.Data: SPM.1:Set ID SPM:SI:R::[1..1]:1..4:: || assume the resource persists from order to report.
Specimen resource defined for the USLab Implementation Guides
Do we need a specimen condition extension?
SPM.2.1:Placer Assigned Identifier:EI_GU:RE::::: ||This would be placer sid for DO and DR filler will use Accessoin IDs

In the test ordering workflow this would be the orderer's specimen identifer(Placer Specimen ID). In the context of the lab test reporting workflow, this could be both the orderer's specimen identifer and the laboratory assigned specimen identifier (Filler Specimen ID).
For Laboratory reporting this element is required.
SPM.4:Specimen Type:CWE_CRE:R::[1..1]:::Specimen Type Value Set limit to Snomed Ct specimen heirarchy for draft
SNOMED Clinical Terms is a systematically organized computer processable collection of medical terms providing codes, terms, synonyms and definitions used in clinical documentation and reporting.
The SNOMED-CT 'preferred name' is preferred although any SNOMED-CT 'synonym' can also be used. ( ihtsdo.org/snomed-ct/)
SPM.4.9:Original Text:ST:C(R/RE):::1..199:#: ||If this exists, this is the text to be used for display.
Used when the laboratory define how the display text if different from the code display text.
This is the laboratory defined display text for the actual test result, if different from the code display names
SPM.18:Specimen Received Date/Time:TS_5:R::[1..1]::: ||this is not known in DO so can't be 1..1 but is always known for DR invarinet for datetime to at least the day
Minimum precision is to the day
For Laboratory reporting this element is required.
